<br>
my advice if you're gonna do this quest is to bring a full group for teh final step, with enough people you have a good chance that someone will bear through the massive lag and crazy mixed aggro long enough to down fergul without the brood killing everyone  - beware tho because when you nuke fergul the broodmother will (if you're unlucky like me) teleport onto your head and beat you down <br>
<br>
as far as the corpses poofing tho i guess verant will have to fix that problem im hoping that they replace my control harness at least though, wish me luck in getting some help with that:) <p><IMG SRC=http://www.westol.com/~target/exepic/exedsig1.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujerichostormbringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jericho Stormbringer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/8/01 12:19:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromniff Military Leggings</span><hr size=1> I did this quest a couple days ago, with a 59 monk and 60 ranger with me for the last fight with Fergul.  When I handed in the Harness of Control, I invised and followed her to the fort.<br>
